Conventional Expectations 
    -> define root that points to a controller#action
    -> have appropriate named controller 
    -> have appropriate named action/method
    -> if done under views rails expects a pages folder 

Generate new conroler from command line
    -> rails genrate controler -controllerName-

start rails app 
 --> rails new ~/directory/app-name
 --> rails s starts server 
 --> yarn start

 deploy to heroku 
  --> heroku login
  --> heroku create 
  --> git push heroku main 

  Database 
  --> has many tables
  ---> collumns
    --> id 
